@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #4A6FA5
  LifeLineBorderColor #4A6FA5
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F0FA
  ParticipantBorderColor #4A6FA5
}

title Revoking an operator via approve_for_all (vulnerable v0.2.0 H-01)

actor Owner
participant "NFT contract\napprove_for_all" as C
participant "Soroban host\n(storage TTL)" as H

Owner -> C : approve_for_all(owner, operator,\n  live_until_ledger = 0)
note right of Owner
  live_until_ledger = 0 is the
  documented way to REVOKE.
end note

C -> C : remove operator from the\napproved-operators list

C -> C : live_for =\nlive_until_ledger - e.ledger().sequence()\n= 0 - seq
note right of C
  Both are u32. 0 - seq underflows
  to ~4.29e9 instead of a small value.
end note

C -> H : extend_ttl(key, live_for, live_for)\nwith live_for ~= u32::MAX
H -->x C : panic: requested TTL exceeds\nthe maximum allowed
note over C, H #FADBD8
  The whole transaction reverts.
  Revocation is impossible.
end note

C -->x Owner : transaction failed

@enduml
